SocketChat-JavaFX is a lightweight LAN chat application built in Java using TCP sockets and JavaFX for its graphical interface.
It enables multiple users connected to the same network to chat in real time ‚Äî no external servers or internet access required.

This project demonstrates practical networking concepts (sockets, I/O streams, threading) combined with a modern GUI layer, making it a perfect reference for learning Java network programming and JavaFX.

‚ú® Features

Real-time local network (LAN) messaging

Host or join chat sessions dynamically

Clean and responsive JavaFX UI

Multi-client support

Works on Windows, macOS, and Linux

Modular code structure ‚Äî easy to extend (add encryption, usernames, timestamps, etc.)

